'''蜻蜓44星系'''是[[后髮座星系團|后髮座星系團]]中的一個[[超稀疏星系|超稀疏星系]]<ref name=Phys.org-2015-05-14>{{cite web|url=http://phys.org/news/2015-05-scientists-fluffiest-galaxies.html|title=Scientists discover the fluffiest galaxies|date=14 May 2015|publisher=[[phys.org|phys.org]]|access-date=2016-08-31|archive-date=2016-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826180254/http://phys.org/news/2015-05-scientists-fluffiest-galaxies.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=Van Dokkum, Pieter et al. |title=Forty-seven milky way-sized, extremely diffuse galaxies in the Coma-Cluster |url=http://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/2041-8205/798/2/L45/meta |date=7 January 2015 |journal=[[天文物理期刊|The Astrophysical Journal Letters]] |accessdate=31 August 2016 |archive-date=2017-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606022434/http://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/2041-8205/798/2/L45/meta |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sci-news.com/astronomy/dragonfly-44-ultra-diffuse-galaxy-dark-matter-04135.html |title=Dragonfly 44: Ultra-Diffuse Galaxy Made Mostly of Dark Matter. Aug 2016 |access-date=2016-08-31 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112041432/http://www.sci-news.com/astronomy/dragonfly-44-ultra-diffuse-galaxy-dark-matter-04135.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。根據觀測其旋轉速度判斷其質量為一萬億[[太阳质量|太阳质量]]，約和[[银河系|银河系]]的質量相同。這也和周圍觀測到的90個[[球狀星團|球狀星團]]一致。不過此星系發出的光只有銀河系的1%<ref>{{cite news|last1=Crosswell|first1=Ken|title=The Milky Way’s dark twin revealed|url=http://www.nature.com/news/the-milky-way-s-dark-twin-revealed-1.20333|accessdate=30 July 2016|publisher=[[自然_(期刊)|Nature]] News|date=26 July 2016|archive-date=2016-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161013105548/http://www.nature.com/news/the-milky-way-s-dark-twin-revealed-1.20333|dead-url=no}}</ref>。該星系由[[蜻蜓望遠鏡頭陣列|蜻蜓望遠鏡頭陣列]]（Dragonfly Telephoto Array）發現<ref name=WashPost-2016-08-25>{{cite news |url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2016/08/25/a-new-class-of-galaxy-has-been-discovered-one-made-almost-entirely-of-dark-matter/ |title= A new class of galaxy has been discovered, one made almost entirely of dark matter |author= Rachel Feltman |date= 25 August 2016 |publisher= Washington Post |accessdate= 2016-11-01 |archive-date= 2020-12-02 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201202074346/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2016/08/25/a-new-class-of-galaxy-has-been-discovered-one-made-almost-entirely-of-dark-matter |dead-url= no }}</ref>。

2016年8月時，科學家指出蜻蜓44星系幾乎完全是由[[暗物质|暗物质]]組成<ref name="AJL-20160825">{{cite journal |author=Van Dokkum, Pieter et al. |title=A High Stellar Velocity Dispersion and ~100 Globular Clusters For The Ultra-Diffuse Galaxy Dragonfly 44 |url=http://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.3847/2041-8205/828/1/L6 |date=25 August 2016 |work=[[天文物理期刊|The Astrophysical Journal Letters]] |accessdate=27 August 2016 |archive-date=2019-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830183131/https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.3847/2041-8205/828/1/L6 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NS-20160825">{{cite web |last=Hall |first=Shannon |title=Ghost galaxy is 99.99 per cent dark matter with almost no stars |url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/2102584-ghost-galaxy-is-99-99-per-cent-dark-matter-with-almost-no-stars/ |date=25 August 2016 |work=[[新科學人|New Scientist]] |accessdate=27 August 2016 |archive-date=2019-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411133536/https://www.newscientist.com/article/2102584-ghost-galaxy-is-99-99-per-cent-dark-matter-with-almost-no-stars/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="WP-20160826">{{cite news |last=Feltman |first=Rachael |title=A new class of galaxy has been discovered, one made almost entirely of dark matter |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2016/08/25/a-new-class-of-galaxy-has-been-discovered-one-made-almost-entirely-of-dark-matter |date=26 August 2016 |work=[[华盛顿邮报|The Washington Post]] |accessdate=26 August 2016 |archive-date=2018-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180402125700/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2016/08/25/a-new-class-of-galaxy-has-been-discovered-one-made-almost-entirely-of-dark-matter/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

